Using atorvastatin with estradiol can raise your blood levels of estradiol because atorvastatin may interfere with the body's elimination of estradiol. In studies, atorvastatin was found to increase the amount of estradiol in the bloodstream by about 20%. It's not totally understood what this may mean to your health, but it's something important to be aware of, particularly as your healthcare provider is working to find the right dosage for medications like estradiol.

Discuss with your doctor the possibility of dose adjustment and increased frequency of testing.
